The paper concerns lower bounds and algorithms for approximation problems in graph theory, specifically Set-Cover, Group Steiner Tree, Directed Steiner Tree, Covering Steiner Tree, and Connected Polymatroid. These topics are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT).
